<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Matrix Chain Multiplication</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Matrix Chain Multiplication</h1>
        <form action="/calculate" method="POST">
            <label for="dimensions">Matrix Dimensions (e.g., 10, 30, 5, 60)</label>
            <input type="text" id="dimensions" name="dimensions" value="<%= dimensions ? dimensions.join(', ') : '' %>" required>
            <button type="submit">Calculate</button>
        </form>
        <% if (minScalarMultiplications !== null) { %>
            <h2>Results:</h2>
            <p>Minimum Scalar Multiplications: <%= minScalarMultiplications %></p>
            <p>Optimal Parenthesization: <%= optimalParenthesization %></p>
        <% } %>
        <div class="explanation">
            <h2>Sample explanation :</h2>
            <p>Matrix chain multiplication is a common optimization problem where we want to find the most efficient way to multiply a sequence of matrices to minimize the total number of scalar multiplications required to compute their product.</p>
            <h2>Example:</h2>
            <p>If input dimensions are: 10,30,5,60,10 then matrix dimension representation will be like this :</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Matrix A1: 10 x 30</li>
                <li>Matrix A2: 30 x 5</li>
                <li>Matrix A3: 5 x 60</li>
                <li>Matrix A4: 60 x 10</li>
            </ul>
            <p>We used dynamic programming to calculate the optimal parenthesization, which determines the order in which the matrices should be multiplied to reduce computational cost.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
